---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { APP_NAME, DEVELOPER_NAME, ANDROID_PACKAGE_ID, IOS_BUNDLE_ID } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout title={`Terms of Use (EULA) — ${APP_NAME}`} description={`Terms of Use and End User License Agreement for the ${APP_NAME} mobile app on Android and iOS, including auto-renewing subscriptions.`}>
	<main class="compliance-main">
		<div class="compliance-panel">

			<a href="/" class="back-link">
				<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="19" y1="12" x2="5" y2="12"/><polyline points="12 19 5 12 12 5"/></svg>
				<span>Back to Home</span>
			</a>

			<div class="page-header">
				<div class="icon-badge icon-badge--violet">
					<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon--violet"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>
				</div>
				<h1 class="serif">Terms of Use (EULA)</h1>
			</div>

			<div class="prose-body prose">

				<p class="last-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 26, 2026</p>

				<section>
					<h2>1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
					<p>By downloading, installing, or using {APP_NAME}, you agree to these Terms of Use (End User License Agreement) and our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the app.</p>
					<p>{APP_NAME} is published by <strong>Cats Build Ltd</strong> trading as <strong>{DEVELOPER_NAME}</strong>. These terms apply to the {APP_NAME} mobile app on <strong>Android</strong> (<code>{ANDROID_PACKAGE_ID}</code>) and <strong>iOS</strong> (<code>{IOS_BUNDLE_ID}</code>), and to this website where relevant.</p>
					<p>If you obtained {APP_NAME} through the Apple App Store, Section 15 also applies. The App Store is not a party to this agreement.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
					<p>{APP_NAME} is a mobile video editing app that helps you turn raw clips into a finished cut by layering animated text, icons, shapes, visual effects, and sound effects on top of your footage — timed to the action. Your original video stays intact; polish is added as overlays, not by regenerating the video.</p>
					<p>Features may include AI-assisted shot analysis, visual effects generation, sound effects generation, project sync, and subscription plans with monthly effect allowances. We may add, change, or remove features over time.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>3. Account Registration</h2>
					<p>To use cloud sync, AI features, and subscriptions, you must create an account with a valid email address. Authentication is provided by <strong>Supabase</strong>. You agree that:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>You are responsible for all activity under your account.</li>
						<li>You will keep your sign-in credentials secure.</li>
						<li>The information you provide is accurate and up to date.</li>
					</ul>
					<p>You must be at least <strong>13 years old</strong> (or the minimum age required in your country) to use {APP_NAME}. If you are under 18, you represent that you have your parent or legal guardian's permission.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 id="subscriptions">4. Subscriptions &amp; Billing</h2>

					<h3>4.1 Subscription plans</h3>
					<p>{APP_NAME} offers auto-renewing subscriptions, including <strong>Creator</strong> and <strong>Pro</strong>. Subscriptions provide access to premium features and a monthly AI effect allowance for the billing period shown at purchase (typically one month). The exact subscription title, length, price, and any introductory or free-trial offer are displayed in the app before you confirm purchase.</p>
					<p>Subscription status is managed through <strong>RevenueCat</strong>. We do not receive or store your full payment card number.</p>

					<h3>4.2 Auto-renewing subscriptions (iOS — Apple App Store)</h3>
					<p>If you subscribe on iOS, the following applies:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Payment will be charged to your <strong>Apple ID account</strong> at confirmation of purchase (or at the end of any free trial or introductory period, if applicable).</li>
						<li>Your subscription <strong>automatically renews</strong> unless auto-renew is turned off at least <strong>24 hours</strong> before the end of the current billing period.</li>
						<li>Your account will be charged for renewal within <strong>24 hours</strong> prior to the end of the current period at the <strong>then-current subscription price</strong> shown in the App Store for that plan.</li>
						<li>You can manage subscriptions and turn off auto-renewal after purchase in <strong>Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions</strong> on your device.</li>
						<li>You may not cancel the current active subscription period; cancelling stops renewal for the next period only.</li>
						<li>If a <strong>free trial</strong> or introductory offer is available, any unused portion will be <strong>forfeited</strong> when you purchase a subscription to that plan, where applicable.</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.3 Auto-renewing subscriptions (Android — Google Play)</h3>
					<p>If you subscribe on Android, the following applies:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Payment will be charged to your <strong>Google Play account</strong> at confirmation of purchase (or at the end of any free trial or introductory period, if applicable).</li>
						<li>Your subscription <strong>automatically renews</strong> unless you cancel at least <strong>24 hours</strong> before the end of the current billing period.</li>
						<li>Your account will be charged for renewal within <strong>24 hours</strong> prior to the end of the current period at the <strong>then-current subscription price</strong> shown in Google Play for that plan.</li>
						<li>You can manage subscriptions and turn off auto-renewal after purchase in <strong>Google Play → Subscriptions</strong>.</li>
						<li>You may not cancel the current active subscription period; cancelling stops renewal for the next period only.</li>
						<li>If a <strong>free trial</strong> or introductory offer is available, any unused portion will be <strong>forfeited</strong> when you purchase a subscription to that plan, where applicable.</li>
					</ul>

					<h3>4.4 Cancellations, refunds, and account deletion</h3>
					<p>Cancel anytime in <strong>Google Play → Subscriptions</strong> (Android) or <strong>Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions</strong> (iOS). Deleting your {APP_NAME} account does not cancel store billing — cancel in the store first if needed.</p>
					<p>Refunds are handled by Google or Apple under their respective policies. We do not control third-party refund decisions.</p>
					<p>For how we handle purchase and subscription data, see our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
				</section>

